# Design System Rules

## 1. Component Anatomy
- All components must be accessible (Radix UI primitives preferred).
- Use `lucide-react` for default icons, but allow icons to be passed as `children` or props (Dependency Injection) for flexibility.
- Components must be agnostic of business logic and data fetching.

## 2. Tailwind v4 & Theming
- Do not use `tailwind.config.js`. Follow Tailwind v4 CSS-first configuration.
- Components MUST NOT contain hardcoded colors (e.g., `bg-blue-500`).
- Strictly use semantic tokens (e.g., `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-destructive`).
- Theming is controlled by the consumer app via CSS variables (e.g., `--primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;`).

## 3. Shadcn Registry Pattern
- Structure components so they can be exported as a Shadcn Custom Registry.
- Primitives live in `/src/registry/ui`.
- Composites live in `/src/registry/composites`.

## 4. Quality Assurance
- Every component must include a `.stories.tsx` file (Storybook).
- Every component must include a `.test.tsx` file (Vitest / React Testing Library).
- Leave space for i18n (React Intl, next-intl, or standard translation dictionaries) where text is unavoidable.